how can i get the current day of the week in js
In JavaScript, you can use the `Date` object to get the current day of the week. Here's an example:

```js
const daysOfWeek = ["Sunday", "Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", "Friday", "Saturday"];
const currentDate = new Date();
const currentDayOfWeek = currentDate.getDay();

console.log('Today is ' + daysOfWeek[currentDayOfWeek]);
```

In this example, `currentDate.getDay()` returns a number between 0 and 6, where 0 represents Sunday, 1 represents Monday, and so on. We use this number to access the corresponding day name from the `daysOfWeek` array.

Running this code will log the current day of the week to the console.
